# ======================================================================
# SHELL SEARCH MODERNIZATION
# Changes default history maneuvering with arrow keys.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
#   [A  up
#   [B  down
#   [5~ page up
#   [6~ page down
"\e[A":  history-search-backward
"\e[B":  history-search-forward
"\C-p":  history-search-backward
"\C-n":  history-search-forward
"\e[5~": previous-history
"\e[6~": next-history
"\C-x\C-l": complete
"\C-x\C-n": menu-complete
"\C-x\C-p": menu-complete-backward
# ======================================================================
## Suggested for those with Macs that have option send Esc:
# "\e\C-w": backward-kill-word
# "\e\C-k": kill-region
# ======================================================================
## My Favorites:
# These can all be listed with $ bind -p
# \C-x\C-e: edit-and-execute-command
# \e\C-e:   shell-expand-line
#   \e-d:   kill-word
#   \e-t:   shell-transpose-words
#   \C-h:   backward-delete-char
# \e\C-h:   backward-kill-word
# \e\C-w:   backward-kill-word
# \C-x!:    possible-command-completions
# \C-x/:    possible-filename-completions
# \C-x@:    possible-hostname-completions
# \C-x~:    possible-username-completions
# \C-x$:    possible-variable-completions
# \C-x\C-r: re-read-init-file
# \C-x\C-u: undo (also \C-_)
# \C-x\C-x: exchange-point-and-mark (point is where the cursor is)
# \C-@:     set-mark
# \M-<space>: set-mark
# \C-]:     character-search
# \M-\C-]:  character-search-backward
